#. <section class="sutta" id="sn2.2"><article><div class="hgroup"><p class="division">
msgctxt "sn2.2:0.1"
msgid "Saṃyutta Nikāya 2"
msgstr "Linked Discourses 2"

#. </p><p>
msgctxt "sn2.2:0.2"
msgid "1. Paṭhamavagga"
msgstr "1. The First Chapter"

#. </p><h1>
msgctxt "sn2.2:0.3"
msgid "2. Dutiyakassapasutta"
msgstr "2. With Kassapa (2nd)"

#. </h1></div><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc1"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.2:1.1"
msgid "Sāvatthinidānaṃ."
msgstr "At Sāvatthī."

msgctxt "sn2.2:1.2"
msgid ""
"Ekamantaṃ ṭhito kho kassapo devaputto bhagavato santike imaṃ gāthaṃ abhāsi:"
msgstr ""
"Standing to one side, the god Kassapa recited this verse in the Buddha’s "
"presence:"

#. </p><blockquote class="gatha"><p>
#. <a class="sc" id="sc2"></a>
msgctxt "sn2.2:2.1"
msgid "“Bhikkhu siyā jhāyī vimuttacitto,"
msgstr "“Suppose a mendicant is one who practices absorption, freed in mind."

# I take the phrase as a poetic abbreviation of the stock hadayassa santi
#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.2:2.2"
msgid "Ākaṅkhe ce hadayassānupattiṃ;"
msgstr "If they want to reach the heart’s peace,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.2:2.3"
msgid "Lokassa ñatvā udayabbayañca,"
msgstr "having known the arising and passing of the world,"

#. <br>
msgctxt "sn2.2:2.4"
msgid "Sucetaso anissito tadānisaṃso”ti."
msgstr "healthy-minded, independent, that is their reward.”"
